<subSubSection id="D0EB0E0D12AF2E0BE90194E4D6AA5A00" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="14" pageNumber="107" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="94784960C2670D17AB8DA236833E62C6" pageId="14" pageNumber="107">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="10E66A73CBC0F88F2C97073C8C64DE66" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="14" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName id="E46CF364667C34CA2124E370A8539519" authorityName="Silveira" authorityYear="1898" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella chromatophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="14" pageNumber="107" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="chromatophylla">
<emphasis id="086A4E1A5030BC788810FC816FC1D7E5" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="107">Selaginella chromatophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was subsumed under 
<taxonomicName id="39CF950DF2A7674D47BFEAD9F68C89C9" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella marginata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="14" pageNumber="107" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="54003DEC6435EC98D6BA76057AA8A560" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="107">Selaginella marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Humb. &amp; Bonpl. ex Willd.) Spring by 
<bibRefCitation id="DEE398D23D8FDFF414E7D6AE27EDBF45" author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Feddes Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="303 - 319" publicationUrl="10.1002/fedr.19360402005" refId="B1" refString="Alston, AHG, 1936. The Brazilian species of Selaginella. Feddes Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 40: 303 - 319, DOI: 10.1002/fedr.19360402005" title="The Brazilian species of Selaginella." url="10.1002/fedr.19360402005" volume="40" year="1936">Alston (1936)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2AF38BB160268BFC5CE23127411EE1F5" author="Reed, CF" journalOrPublisher="Memorias da Sociedade Broteriana" pageId="20" pageNumber="113" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B21" refString="Reed, CF, 1965-1966. Index Selaginellarum. Memorias da Sociedade Broteriana 18: 1 - 287" title="Index Selaginellarum." volume="18" year="1965 - 1966">Reed (1965-1966)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="752CE932BF6A5A352BCF93D0635CF054" author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B2" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany 9: 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. (1981)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="B480BA1237D6C79E32A0DDD5C4C98504" author="Hirai, RY" journalOrPublisher="Revista Brasileira de Botanica" pageId="20" pageNumber="113" pagination="313 - 339" publicationUrl="10.1590/S0100-84042000000300007" refId="B9" refString="Hirai, RY, Prado, J, 2000. Selaginellaceae Willk. no Estado de Sao Paulo, Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Botanica 23: 313 - 339, DOI: 10.1590/S0100-84042000000300007" title="Selaginellaceae Willk. no Estado de Sao Paulo, Brasil." url="10.1590/S0100-84042000000300007" volume="23" year="2000">Hirai and Prado (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. As currently circumscribed, however, 
<taxonomicName id="B401F2B34F0CABD066C9BF12B86C58A0" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella marginata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="14" pageNumber="107" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="F9082FF67AC21785A84E754131AF619C" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="107">Selaginella marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically variable and ill-defined. My preliminary revisionary work on 
<taxonomicName id="59DEF2B44F4E48EF0D6C892EC0508028" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella marginata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="14" pageNumber="107" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="336E2EE63429A8D1D9E49E5887799FC0" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="107">Selaginella marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including SEM studies of leaves and spores, indicates it is a species complex (here termed the &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="319D59236283EA466713B6188C022D7D" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella marginata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="14" pageNumber="107" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="F34BB3E24F7B98462A31275317DFCA5A" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="107">Selaginella marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex&quot;) that could include, at least, five taxa (Valdespino in prep.). Among these, 
<taxonomicName id="88F2BCC286A47C2175E4419A52F9085C" authorityName="Silveira" authorityYear="1898" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella chromatophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="14" pageNumber="107" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="chromatophylla">
<emphasis id="86415525BC48689536A0BE4013255A59" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="107">Selaginella chromatophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AFA3AF31C9D105C6D67B7CDB9EC9C08B" authorityName="W. R. Buck" authorityYear="1986" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella parviarticulata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="14" pageNumber="107" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="parviarticulata">
<emphasis id="3793132C197E5F08AFD376C426DEE0ED" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="107">Selaginella parviarticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Buck are very similar because of their small leaf size. 
<taxonomicName id="61F97B7C6711340F1F74EB84320C6811" authorityName="Silveira" authorityYear="1898" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella chromatophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="14" pageNumber="107" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="chromatophylla">
<emphasis id="E64F380643EBFCE0E0F31406328D7C80" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="107">Selaginella chromatophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the latter by its lateral and axillary leaves with peltate (vs. basally attached) bases, lateral leaves with acroscopic margins short-ciliate along proximal 
<normalizedToken id="441E82883120E5EE06E35F36C08AB12E" originalValue="½">1/2</normalizedToken>
(vs. entire), median leaves with the peltate auricles ciliate (vs. entire or almost so), and microspores gemmate or globular (vs. corrugate). It differs from typical 
<taxonomicName id="5436F19F6C1739057206FDED083E726E" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella marginata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="14" pageNumber="107" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="9C89A3984DBE2DAE48058F99F54C52B1" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="107">Selaginella marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its lateral 
<pageBreakToken id="A78604E95F09AAACBF385D6434678F4F" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" start="start">leaves</pageBreakToken>
broadly ovate-elliptic (vs. ovate-deltate) with the peltate auricles ⅙ (vs. ⅓-
<normalizedToken id="076D562ABF73A4B7A8DE3D31F4BE2538" originalValue="½">1/2</normalizedToken>
) the length of the laminae, both halves of the laminae of equal width (vs. acroscopic halves wider than the basiscopic ones) with obtuse to broadly acute (vs. acuminate) apices, axillary leaves obovate-oblong (vs. ovate-deltate) with obtuse to broadly acute (vs. acuminate) apices, median leaves with acute (vs. long-acuminate) apices, and gemmate or globular (vs. echinulate) microspores. 
<taxonomicName id="27F2FAEFC85DCE530BF106F46ED1BDB9" authorityName="Silveira" authorityYear="1898" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella chromatophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="chromatophylla">
<emphasis id="5F01BF1468008077BB8D2846EEA0D8DA" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella chromatophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs further from the previously discussed 
<taxonomicName id="D61892977D7D32A094A4F1A62AFE3F08" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella marginata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="CCDFD45DA317B99A2822D6C2361DE37C" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B2819BCDCD5117B1B73FDC29D0D20C3B" authorityName="W. R. Buck" authorityYear="1986" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella parviarticulata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="parviarticulata">
<emphasis id="489E578C5F98B59A4629BEBFFE2B17A3" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella parviarticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its stems usually branching in a zig-zag pattern.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ECCBA3CEA3709B3E5AE60CF398AACB02" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">
The name 
<taxonomicName id="C975883B8A182DE1615BDD836B7B586D" authorityName="Silveira" authorityYear="1898" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella chromatophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="chromatophylla">
<emphasis id="DDA142689378C125A6623D1609817DE5" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella chromatophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is provisionally used here for the taxon documented with specimens cited pending a full nomenclatural and taxonomic revision of the rest of the species in the &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="72394428CFE41BD9C4316BA4AD510103" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella marginata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="6C636010FF1A573BD52B01D453B1640D" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex&quot;. Other names that could potentially apply to that taxon are 
<taxonomicName id="335197357FC1D1F0E394CC7BAF73C34D" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella excurrens" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="excurrens">
<emphasis id="35D5FD04E4F29DACAE03120C339410A7" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella excurrens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Spring and 
<taxonomicName id="D774857DD6544306D54227A43AC232F4" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella distorta" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="distorta">
<emphasis id="61E3FDE83A481F801A78D00A1C132711" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella distorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Spring) Spring, which if proven to be conspecific would both have priority over 
<taxonomicName id="DEFD2F02473963A488C582B00961EC67" authorityName="Silveira" authorityYear="1898" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella chromatophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="chromatophylla">
<emphasis id="38FF7E8D38F84FEF5C0A162B90E9B087" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella chromatophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
